{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WhNeJutb5KiNGfb6beskRt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The precondition probe succeeded, which means the state was already \"ready\" from a previous stage. The precondition in `nginx_env_ready` is:\n- on_probe_fail: skip (so if probe fails, it runs the apply steps; if probe succeeds, it skips to verify)\n- probe: checks if demo namespace is Active AND curl-test is ready\n- if probe passes, it skips straight to verify\n\nSo the precondition found demo ns Active and curl-test ready, so it skipped the whole apply sequence (which would have set up ingress-nginx with two classes, ingress-gateway, etc.).\n\nThis explains why the cluster state is incomplete:\n- Missing the second controller and ingress-gateway service\n- demo-app ingress still has the `nginx` class from stage_01 instead of the expected configuration\n- IngressClasses don't include the ingress-1 and ingress-2 variants\n\nThe test needs a curl to `http://ingress-gateway.demo.svc.cluster.local/` with `Host: class.example.com` to return \"hello\", and the demo Ingress needs the correct ingress class set. The oracle validates this requirement.\n\nLet me check what the oracle actually expects to pass.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":569,"cache_read_input_tokens":37427,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":569},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e3dba6c-63c9-46eb-8902-73b2751b7027","uuid":"37a18476-464b-4de0-aa2b-b0e4ebb1fc17","request_id":"req_011CcQTvZactxWDYr1TLfR4h"}
